<subSubSection id="C3606530B31E8A08FF68FD4CFD4AFA6B" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC536BBB31E8A08FF68FD4CFD4AFA6B" blockId="13.[181,782,594,1515]" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B4AB31E8A08FF68FD4CFEF7FD71" author="Schulz, O. E." box="[210,366,727,753]" editor="I. Urban" journalOrPublisher="Symbolae Antillanae" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" pagination="140 - 279" part="6" refId="ref14448" refString="Schulz, O. E. 1909. Solanacearum genera nonnulla, in I. Urban (ed.) Symbolae Antillanae 6: 140 - 279." title="Solanacearum genera nonnulla" type="journal article" year="1909">Schulz (1909)</bibRefCitation>
cited three collections in his original description of 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FEDBFD63FC9EFC92" box="[353,775,760,786]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FEDBFD63FDFBFC92" authorityName="O. E. Schulz, Linden" authorityYear="1944" box="[353,610,760,786]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyneurum">Solanum pachyneurum</taxonomicName>
– Wright 382
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FF0FFC81FED8FCB3" box="[181,321,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Eggers 5197</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FE3AFC82FD8BFCB3" box="[384,530,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Linden 1944</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FD99FC82FD3FFCB3" box="[547,678,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Wright 382</emphasis>
, original material of both 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FECFFCA1FDEBFCD4" authorityName="O. E. Schulz, Linden" authorityYear="1944" box="[373,626,826,852]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyneurum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FECFFCA1FDEBFCD4" box="[373,626,826,852]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Solanum pachyneurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FD16FCA1FE5CFCF5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pachyneurum" variety="glabrescens">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FD16FCA1FE95FCF5" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">S. pachyneurum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FEF3FCC0FE5CFCF5" box="[329,453,859,885]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">glabrescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FD3AFCC0FF6EFC17" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyneuroides">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FD3AFCC0FF6EFC17" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">S. pachyneuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see above), consists of a series of mixed sheets of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FF6DFC05FE16FC38" authorityName="O. E. Schulz, Linden" authorityYear="1944" box="[215,399,926,952]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyneurum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FF6DFC05FE16FC38" box="[215,399,926,952]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">S. pachyneurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FE75FC05FD05FC38" box="[463,668,926,952]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyneuroides">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FE75FC05FD05FC38" box="[463,668,926,952]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">S. pachyneuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is not clear whether the two taxa occur sympatrically, or whether Wright assigned his numbers to plants collected after the fact, common practice at the time (and very likely). The latter case is suggested by the labeling of the sheet of 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FEDEFBD8FE7CFBDD" box="[356,485,1091,1117]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Wright 382</emphasis>
at GH (see 
<figureCitation id="13412A3EB31E8A08FDCCFBD8FD52FBDD" box="[630,715,1091,1117]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[151,185,1827,1848]" captionTargetBox="[204,1353,205,1804]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 4. a, lectotype of Solanum orthacanthum O.E. Schulz, Fuertes 1890 (A00077559). Reproduced with permission of Harvard University,Cambridge,Massachusetts,USA;b, lectotype of S. pachyneurum O.E.Schulz var.glabrescens O.E.Schulz,Wright 382 p.p.(left hand stems of GH00112906) (= S. pachyneuroides). Reproduced with permission of Harvard University, Cambridge, Massachusetts, USA; c, lectotype of S. pachyneurum O.E. Schulz,Linden 1944 (K000196232). Reproduced with permission of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew; d, lectotype of S. polygamum Vahl var. thomae O. Kuntze, Kuntze 36 (NY0074477) (= S. polygamum). Reproduced with permission of the New York Botanical Garden." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6326316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6326316/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
). The sheet that Schulz examined in B has been destroyed, and other sheets of 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FE09FB1DFDA7FB20" box="[435,574,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Wright 382</emphasis>
are mostly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FD43FB1DFED3FB41" authorityName="O. E. Schulz, Linden" authorityYear="1944" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyneurum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FD43FB1DFED3FB41" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">S. pachyneurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but some are a mixture of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FD3EFB3CFF7AFB62" authorityName="O. E. Schulz, Linden" authorityYear="1944" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyneurum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FD3EFB3CFF7AFB62" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">S. pachyneurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FEA5FB53FE7FFB62" box="[287,486,1224,1250]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyneuroides">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FEA5FB53FE7FFB62" box="[287,486,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">S. pachyneuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above). For this reason, it is more sensible to choose one of the many other syntypes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FEEBFA91FE66FAA4" authorityName="O. E. Schulz, Linden" authorityYear="1944" box="[337,511,1290,1316]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyneurum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FEEBFA91FE66FAA4" box="[337,511,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">S. pachyneurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the lectotype to avoid confusion. A sheet of 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FE13FAB0FDAFFAC5" box="[425,566,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Linden 1944</emphasis>
was not found at B and is presumably destroyed, but well preserved duplicates have been located at BM and K. Neither the K nor the BM sheet has any locality data, but the sheet at K (
<figureCitation id="13412A3EB31E8A08FF62FA2BFEBCFA4A" box="[216,293,1456,1482]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[151,185,1827,1848]" captionTargetBox="[204,1353,205,1804]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 4. a, lectotype of Solanum orthacanthum O.E. Schulz, Fuertes 1890 (A00077559). Reproduced with permission of Harvard University,Cambridge,Massachusetts,USA;b, lectotype of S. pachyneurum O.E.Schulz var.glabrescens O.E.Schulz,Wright 382 p.p.(left hand stems of GH00112906) (= S. pachyneuroides). Reproduced with permission of Harvard University, Cambridge, Massachusetts, USA; c, lectotype of S. pachyneurum O.E. Schulz,Linden 1944 (K000196232). Reproduced with permission of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew; d, lectotype of S. polygamum Vahl var. thomae O. Kuntze, Kuntze 36 (NY0074477) (= S. polygamum). Reproduced with permission of the New York Botanical Garden." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6326316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6326316/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
) is better preserved, has reproductive parts and has therefore been selected as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
